{%- comment -%}
  Base card primitive (spec §4/§5.2: Surface/Card-tint plane, radius-card, hover
  lift). Handles the simple "whole card links somewhere" case directly.

  Composite cards with internal structure (product-card, blog-card, testimonial
  card, etc. — later milestones) are expected to apply the `.card` / `.card--padded`
  / `.card--interactive` classes to their own markup directly rather than force
  their layout through this snippet's single-content-block shape; Liquid snippets
  have no real "slot" mechanism, so trying to genericize a multi-region card here
  would just reintroduce the duplication this system is trying to avoid.

  Accepts:
  - content (required): pre-rendered HTML/text, typically built with {% capture %}.
  - href: optional link destination — renders <a> when present, <div> otherwise.
  - interactive: bool, adds the hover-lift shadow transition. Defaults to true
    when `href` is present, false otherwise.
  - padded: bool, adds internal spacing. Defaults to true.
{%- endcomment -%}
{%- liquid
  assign card_tag = 'div'
  if href
    assign card_tag = 'a'
  endif

  assign card_interactive = interactive
  if interactive == blank and href
    assign card_interactive = true
  endif

  assign card_padded = padded
  if padded == blank
    assign card_padded = true
  endif

  assign card_class = 'card'
  if card_interactive
    assign card_class = card_class | append: ' card--interactive'
  endif
  if card_padded
    assign card_class = card_class | append: ' card--padded'
  endif
-%}
<{{ card_tag }}{% if href %} href="{{ href }}"{% endif %} class="{{ card_class }}">
  {{ content }}
</{{ card_tag }}>
